00:21:01,527 --> 00:21:04,917
Excuse me. lf he is to be sacrificed
before Kaili,

251
00:21:05,047 --> 00:21:06,719
why is he not painted red?

252
00:21:06,847 --> 00:21:12,479
l've never had the courage to ask him,
but as he's my best friend l will.

253
00:21:14,647 --> 00:21:18,037
- What's this? Glasses?
- That's right, sir. Glasses.

254
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:22,001
A victim is offered
to the dread Kaili everyday.

255
00:21:22,127 --> 00:21:23,958
All are happy to go.

256
00:21:24,087 --> 00:21:27,363
He who wins is privileged to wear
the sacred ring

257
00:21:27,487 --> 00:21:29,955
from sun to moon,
from moon to sun.

258
00:21:30,087 --> 00:21:33,762
And at the end of the happy day
he is slaughtered jolly with a knife.

259
00:21:33,887 --> 00:21:38,563
And sacrificed jolly with a knife,
so l'm told, with that ring.

260
00:21:38,687 --> 00:21:40,086
Three hours to live.

261
00:21:40,207 --> 00:21:43,756
- (Man) You have till five o'clock.
- Before a new victim is chosen.

262
00:21:43,887 --> 00:21:46,879
You are lucky to be chosen!

263
00:21:47,007 --> 00:21:50,556
My old mum would give her right hand
to be chosen.

264
00:21:51,647 --> 00:21:54,957
- What's this?
- A season ticket.

265
00:21:55,087 --> 00:21:58,159
l like a lot of seasoning in my soup.

266
00:22:00,887 --> 00:22:02,843
There's somebody been in this soup.

267
00:22:02,967 --> 00:22:06,721
l got it from this Eastern bird... lady...
in a fan letter.

268
00:22:06,847 --> 00:22:09,998
l get all sorts.
Rubbish, though, isn't it? Sacrifice.

269
00:22:11,727 --> 00:22:13,843
No? Come off!

270
00:22:13,967 --> 00:22:17,960
So, get in touch with your authorities
and send back the ring to this lady,

271
00:22:18,087 --> 00:22:20,157
who will then go happy to Kaili.

272
00:22:20,287 --> 00:22:22,084
- Thank you.
- (Bhuta) Three hours.

273
00:22:22,687 --> 00:22:24,723
There's a footprint in here.

274
00:22:24,847 --> 00:22:26,963
Here, you have a go.

275
00:22:28,647 --> 00:22:30,205
(Gasps) Flee!

276
00:22:36,327 --> 00:22:38,716
(Woman screams)

277
00:22:54,607 --> 00:22:58,316
We have lots of little problems like this.
Some of them matrimonial.

278
00:22:58,447 --> 00:22:59,766
(Laughs)

279
00:22:59,887 --> 00:23:01,798
This ring is not stone.

280
00:23:01,927 --> 00:23:05,681
- l've only got three hours to live.
- Therefore, it must be a metal.

281
00:23:13,087 --> 00:23:17,603
- l don't know this metal.
- You're not getting anywhere, are you?

282
00:23:17,727 --> 00:23:21,356
Early days yet, sir.
Therefore it must be an alloy.

283
00:23:21,487 --> 00:23:26,607
There's a certain amount of hurry up
involved here. My life is in danger.

284
00:23:26,727 --> 00:23:28,797
Three ten.

285
00:23:28,927 --> 00:23:30,519
- The wheel.
- Not the wheel.

286
00:23:30,647 --> 00:23:34,959
Even the Royal House of Hanover
had the wheel, sir.

287
00:23:35,087 --> 00:23:37,681
(Whirring)

288
00:23:47,447 --> 00:23:50,120
- l've never seen anything like it.
- You've failed.

289
00:23:50,247 --> 00:23:54,240
- l suggest you see a specialist.
- What kind? Your tools are broken.

290
00:23:54,367 --> 00:23:57,359
The fire brigade once got my head
out of some railings.

291
00:23:57,487 --> 00:24:01,560
- Did you want them to?
- No. l left it there when not at school.

292
00:24:01,687 --> 00:24:03,962
You can see a lot of the world
from railings.

293
00:24:04,087 --> 00:24:06,396
(Electronic beeping)

294
00:24:09,647 --> 00:24:12,480
l like operations,
they give you a sense of outlook.

295
00:24:13,527 --> 00:24:15,245
This won't work.

296
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:18,359
lt could work if the government
would spend more money.

297
00:24:18,487 --> 00:24:20,284
Made in America you see.

298
00:24:21,167 --> 00:24:22,805
Another failure.

299
00:24:22,927 --> 00:24:25,885
The idea is...
The idea as l see it

300
00:24:26,007 --> 00:24:30,125
is that we expand the molecules
and the ring grows bigger and drops off.

301
00:24:30,247 --> 00:24:33,956
- What's your electricity bill like?
- lt's sort of a long counterfoil.

302
00:24:34,087 --> 00:24:36,282
lt's not dropping off.

303
00:24:38,527 --> 00:24:42,202
Voltage!
Voltage...up, up...

304
00:24:42,327 --> 00:24:43,646
Up, up!

305
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:47,316
- Are you sure l'm earthed?
- Oh no, hold on. Thank you.

306
00:24:47,447 --> 00:24:50,484
Made in America.
Streets ahead of anything we've got.

307
00:24:50,607 --> 00:24:52,643
This is English.

308
00:24:52,767 --> 00:24:56,282
- ls it green, the earth in America?
- ln some places it's brown.

309
00:24:56,407 --> 00:24:57,920
He's not earthed.

310
00:24:58,047 --> 00:25:02,040
He's an idiot.
Has a degree in woodwork. l ask you!

311
00:25:05,367 --> 00:25:06,880
Done.

312
00:25:08,527 --> 00:25:10,802
- 5... 4...
- Come on.

313
00:25:11,527 --> 00:25:16,442
3-2-1 -go! l observe the procedure.
He'll thank me for it in the end.

314
00:25:16,567 --> 00:25:18,797
Scientist, you're getting nowhere.

315
00:25:18,927 --> 00:25:22,761
lt's the plugs.
Good British plugs.

316
00:25:22,887 --> 00:25:27,005
All this America rig. Wrong voltage.
That's what foxes me.

317
00:25:27,127 --> 00:25:29,243
- How do you feel?
- l used to use my hands.

318
00:25:29,367 --> 00:25:31,358
He used to use his hands.

319
00:25:33,167 --> 00:25:36,159
- Will he still be able to drum?
- Did he do a lot of it?

320
00:25:36,287 --> 00:25:39,404
- Voltage...up!
- l'm no mean hand at the old sticks.

321
00:25:41,687 --> 00:25:43,439
The voltage, up, up, up!

322
00:25:43,567 --> 00:25:46,877
- Hey, he's calling you. Up, up, up!
- Up, up, up!

323
00:25:48,767 --> 00:25:50,564
The bunker!

324
00:25:52,687 --> 00:25:54,723
(Electronic humming)

325
00:25:59,607 --> 00:26:03,486
- l can't watch.
- lt's working! Give it the gun, Algernon.

326
00:26:03,607 --> 00:26:05,723
(Whirring)

327
00:26:10,887 --> 00:26:12,525
Stop it!

328
00:26:12,647 --> 00:26:14,603
lt's more than my job's worth!

329
00:26:14,727 --> 00:26:17,799
He's out to rule the world
if he can get a government grant.

330
00:26:17,927 --> 00:26:20,839
Outrageous!
You're nothing but a mad scientist!

331
00:26:31,887 --> 00:26:33,525
Fantastic!

332
00:26:33,647 --> 00:26:37,720
With a ring like that l could,
dare l say it, rule the world.

333
00:26:37,847 --> 00:26:40,805
l must have the ring...
Algernon, the laser.

334
00:26:40,927 --> 00:26:44,840
Get your hands off him
or l'll call the Metropolitan scuffers!

335
00:26:44,967 --> 00:26:46,605
The laser...

336
00:26:46,727 --> 00:26:50,515
- Get him off.
- l must have this ring. The laser.

337
00:26:51,247 --> 00:26:56,446
Halt! Release him or l'll shoot
and l am a dead eyeshot shooting.

338
00:26:56,567 --> 00:26:59,001
- l've got it.
- Switch off that machine.

339
00:27:02,367 --> 00:27:04,483
- The laser.
- The laser, yes...

340
00:27:04,607 --> 00:27:07,758
l'm better with animals
than plugs and transistors.

341
00:27:07,887 --> 00:27:11,243
MlT was after me,
wanted me to rule the world for them.

342
00:27:11,367 --> 00:27:13,676
Daddy being the local master
of the hounds.

343
00:27:13,807 --> 00:27:16,799
That's where l get it from,
my love of animals.

344
00:27:16,927 --> 00:27:20,636
They trust me.
l should have been in vivisection.

345
00:27:20,767 --> 00:27:24,555
How do you know we can trust her?
She's had your fingers before, Ringo.

346
00:27:24,687 --> 00:27:27,997
Well, that was a mistake.
l can vouch for her. We're very close.

347
00:27:28,887 --> 00:27:31,526
- Lasers ready.
- Get them!

348
00:27:32,927 --> 00:27:34,918
(Laser Beeps)

349
00:27:35,807 --> 00:27:37,365
(Bang)

350
00:27:38,647 --> 00:27:41,480
lt's the wrong plug...
Just give me five minutes.

351
00:27:43,087 --> 00:27:46,921
lt's the brain drain.
His brain's draining.

352
00:27:50,607 --> 00:27:52,563
( THE BEATLES:
''You've Got to Hide Your Love Away'')

353
00:27:52,687 --> 00:27:56,236
Here l stand with head in hand

354
00:27:56,367 --> 00:27:59,359
Turn my face to the wall

355
00:28:00,487 --> 00:28:04,366
lf she's gone l can't go on

356
00:28:04,487 --> 00:28:09,117
Feeling two foot small

357
00:28:10,367 --> 00:28:14,201
Ev'rywhere people stare

358
00:28:14,327 --> 00:28:17,205
Each and ev'ryday

359
00:28:18,007 --> 00:28:22,000
l can see them laugh at me

360
00:28:22,127 --> 00:28:26,723
And l hear them say

361
00:28:30,047 --> 00:28:35,758
''Hey, you've got to hide
your love away!''

362
00:28:37,847 --> 00:28:42,557
''Hey, you've got to hide
your love away!''

363
00:28:45,607 --> 00:28:49,600
How can l even try?

364
00:28:49,727 --> 00:28:52,719
l can never win

365
00:28:53,727 --> 00:28:57,561
Hearing them, seeing them

366
00:28:57,687 --> 00:29:03,159
ln the state l'm in

367
00:29:03,287 --> 00:29:07,405
How could she say to me

368
00:29:07,527 --> 00:29:10,166
''Love will find a way''?

369
00:29:11,287 --> 00:29:15,121
Gather 'round all you clowns

370
00:29:15,247 --> 00:29:20,367
Let me hear you say

371
00:29:22,967 --> 00:29:28,280
''Hey, you've got to hide
your love away!''

372
00:29:30,807 --> 00:29:36,279
''Hey, you've got to hide
your love away!''

373
00:29:57,047 --> 00:29:58,765
l have here...

374
00:29:58,887 --> 00:30:00,798
(Gasps)

375
00:30:00,927 --> 00:30:03,839
Now see what you've done
with your filthy Eastern ways.

376
00:30:03,967 --> 00:30:07,642
No! lt is Clang, the High Priest,
who is filthy in his ways.

377
00:30:07,767 --> 00:30:11,237
(Posh accent) How do we know
you're not sent by him to nick the ring,

378
00:30:11,367 --> 00:30:13,756
when you've lulled us
with your filthy ways?

379
00:30:13,887 --> 00:30:17,357
- What filthy ways are these?
- You can put that away.

380
00:30:17,487 --> 00:30:21,605
Until this moment you were safe
because my sister was chosen

381
00:30:21,727 --> 00:30:24,560
and no other could be sacrificed
to Kaili.

382
00:30:24,687 --> 00:30:28,316
Now my sister is safe and rises up.

383
00:30:33,567 --> 00:30:35,159
(Soft clang)

384
00:30:35,687 --> 00:30:39,680
(Ahme ) 'And a new day dawns,
a new victim is chosen...'

385
00:30:39,807 --> 00:30:43,686
From this moment it is death to him
who wears the ring.

386
00:30:46,047 --> 00:30:48,515
This will make your finger shrink.
Be brave.

387
00:30:48,647 --> 00:30:50,126
Don't look.

388
00:30:50,247 --> 00:30:53,398
Alas, if he were brave
this would not be necessary.

389
00:30:56,087 --> 00:30:58,362
(Birds chirp)

390
00:31:05,767 --> 00:31:09,123
Where've you been?
You've been up that temple again.

391
00:31:09,247 --> 00:31:13,684
You're as bad as your sister, coming
home from work at all hours and colours.

392
00:31:21,607 --> 00:31:23,757
There might be some insurance.

393
00:31:23,887 --> 00:31:26,640
l wouldn't think of such a thing!
Find out.

394
00:31:26,767 --> 00:31:28,962
What did you say that stuff is?

395
00:31:29,087 --> 00:31:33,205
This will just make his finger shrink
a little. lt's a minor medical secret.

396
00:31:33,327 --> 00:31:35,682
l'm sure there's no call for all this.

397
00:31:35,807 --> 00:31:39,766
l'm allergic to Penicillin
and all them other wonder drugs.

398
00:31:39,887 --> 00:31:43,243
- Gum?
- Are you sure it's not or habit forming?

399
00:31:43,367 --> 00:31:46,086
No. As long as you don't swallow it.

400
00:32:03,807 --> 00:32:06,526
(Whispers) All right.
Synchronise your watches.

401
00:32:06,647 --> 00:32:09,639
You, you, you and you.
Paint him red and then kill him.

402
00:32:16,527 --> 00:32:18,006
Kaili.

403
00:32:18,127 --> 00:32:21,199
Kaili. Kaili.

404
00:32:21,327 --> 00:32:25,559
l promise you
the effect is purely transitory.

405
00:32:25,687 --> 00:32:27,200
lt wears off very quickly.

406
00:32:27,327 --> 00:32:30,876
(Doorbell rings)
(Ahme ) Don't answer it! lt's Clang.

407
00:32:32,047 --> 00:32:33,958
(Hollering and knocking)

408
00:32:34,087 --> 00:32:37,716
- Perhaps it won't take...
- This is a dreadful miscarriage.

409
00:32:37,847 --> 00:32:39,326
(Hollering)

410
00:32:39,447 --> 00:32:41,756
(Ringo ) Come on, my finger!

411
00:32:42,567 --> 00:32:44,398
Where's Paul?

412
00:32:44,527 --> 00:32:48,236
Where's Paul? Come on, Paul,
stop messing about.

413
00:32:49,127 --> 00:32:51,163
Where's he gone?

414
00:32:51,287 --> 00:32:53,642
- Where are you, Paul?
- lt's his best suit.

415
00:33:13,807 --> 00:33:17,482
Don't look right or left. They might take
us for innocent bystanders.

416
00:33:19,887 --> 00:33:21,684
(Baby crying)

417
00:33:24,607 --> 00:33:27,121
- Standby.
- (Whispers) Standby.

418
00:33:27,247 --> 00:33:29,715
Look out!
They're coming through the door!

419
00:33:29,847 --> 00:33:31,997
(Knocking)

420
00:33:36,287 --> 00:33:38,278
- Go!
- Go!

421
00:33:41,927 --> 00:33:44,077
(Yells) Kaili!

422
00:33:50,087 --> 00:33:52,237
Kaili... Oh!

423
00:33:56,487 --> 00:33:58,876
- Sorry, l hit him.
- Oh!

424
00:34:00,887 --> 00:34:03,845
Get me the home office.
He's wrecking my home.

425
00:34:03,967 --> 00:34:06,401
Kaili! Kaili!

426
00:34:08,807 --> 00:34:10,559
(Gasps) Get off!

427
00:34:14,047 --> 00:34:16,959
- lt's me, you fool.
- Oh, sorry.

428
00:34:17,087 --> 00:34:18,725
Well, stop it!

429
00:34:22,367 --> 00:34:24,562
Feet! Feet, you fool!

430
00:35:02,767 --> 00:35:05,759
(Growls)

431
00:35:14,287 --> 00:35:17,438
(Sobs)

432
00:35:19,647 --> 00:35:22,559
Kaili! He's red! Kill him!

433
00:35:26,247 --> 00:35:28,078
(Gunshot)

434
00:35:35,287 --> 00:35:38,199
Oh, my goodness gosh!
Withdraw! Withdraw!

435
00:35:38,327 --> 00:35:40,045
Up!

436
00:35:41,087 --> 00:35:42,759
Up, up, up!

437
00:35:42,887 --> 00:35:44,878
- You!
- Which one has the ring?

438
00:35:45,007 --> 00:35:47,282
That one with the large ned.

439
00:35:47,407 --> 00:35:49,318
Neb!
And it's yours.

440
00:35:49,447 --> 00:35:53,599
- Keep your hands up.
- How can l get it off with my hands up?

441
00:35:54,647 --> 00:35:56,842
ln the name of science
l demand that ring.

442
00:35:56,967 --> 00:35:58,446
lt's yours!

443
00:35:58,567 --> 00:36:01,684
- lt's worth something.
- A couple of bob, at least.

444
00:36:01,807 --> 00:36:06,119
Had to do all this myself... Backward
Britain they call us on Wall Street.

445
00:36:06,247 --> 00:36:10,160
With a ring like that
could l interest the military?

446
00:36:10,287 --> 00:36:11,766
No, l could not.

447
00:36:11,887 --> 00:36:13,957
l can't get it off.

448
00:36:15,607 --> 00:36:17,165
(Squelch)

449
00:36:18,687 --> 00:36:20,917
- Paul?
- Look, what you've done.

450
00:36:21,047 --> 00:36:24,517
- Hey, is that Paul?
- Algernon, my little black bag.

451
00:36:24,647 --> 00:36:26,683
l shall have to operate.

452
00:36:27,727 --> 00:36:30,287
lt'll be on the National Health,
won't it?

453
00:36:30,407 --> 00:36:32,398
- (Whooshing)
- Look!

454
00:36:34,367 --> 00:36:37,359
Ugh! l'm all sticky. You're all red!

455
00:36:37,487 --> 00:36:40,285
- We thought that was you.
- No that's not me.

456
00:36:40,407 --> 00:36:43,205
l'm glad it wore off quickly.

457
00:36:44,007 --> 00:36:45,884
What are you doing here?

458
00:36:47,287 --> 00:36:49,403
- (Hammer clicks)
- Get out!

459
00:36:51,887 --> 00:36:55,960
British, you see! Useless.
lf l had a Luger...

460
00:36:56,087 --> 00:36:59,477
Their scientists are properly equipped.
Think on it.

461
00:36:59,607 --> 00:37:04,442
The remedy is in your hands...
you, the voters.

462
00:37:10,327 --> 00:37:12,363
- Where's Ahme?
- l don't know.

463
00:37:15,967 --> 00:37:20,085
(Speaks in Eastern language )

464
00:37:24,047 --> 00:37:28,006
(Continues speaking
in Eastern language )

465
00:37:28,887 --> 00:37:31,526
- Hai?
- What? Yes... Hai.

466
00:37:31,647 --> 00:37:35,435
(Continues speaking
in Eastern language )

467
00:37:35,567 --> 00:37:38,400
l don't understand a word.
l don't speak the language.

468
00:37:38,527 --> 00:37:40,677
Latin, yes. But this Eastern babble, no.

469
00:37:40,807 --> 00:37:43,275
Ah, the ring! Come on, we go.

470
00:37:59,247 --> 00:38:02,683
